modules.description: This module creates an Lwt-based session manager using a provided backend. It handles session creation, retrieval, and expiration using cookies, with functions to generate, clear, and update sessions based on HTTP headers. It works directly with session keys, values, and expiration periods, integrating cookie management into web workflows.

This module implements an Lwt-based session manager using cookies for stateful web interactions. It provides functions to generate, retrieve, update, and clear sessions by manipulating HTTP headers and cookies, working directly with session keys, values, and expiration times. It is used to manage user sessions in web applications where asynchronous I/O is required.
